org.sql: SELECT users.* FROM users WHERE users.status = "$1" AND users.status = "$2" AND (users.id = 2 OR users.id IN (SELECT user_id FROM members WHERE project_id IN (1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6))) AND users.type IN ("$3", "$4") AND (LOWER(users.login) LIKE LOWER('%autocomp%') OR users.id IN (SELECT user_id FROM email_addresses WHERE LOWER(address) LIKE LOWER('%autocomp%')) OR LOWER(users.firstname) LIKE LOWER('%autocomp%') OR LOWER(users.lastname) LIKE LOWER('%autocomp%')) ORDER BY users.type DESC, users.firstname, users.lastname, users.id LIMIT "$5"
